Ocean photographer Lloyd Meudell started taking images of the sea with a GoPro after being an avid surfer . 
  The 40-year-old takes most of his shots on Kiama beach on the south coast of NSW . 
  He uses an EOS 5D Mark III DSLR and numerous lenses to capture the images . 
  He calls the shots 'foam surrealism' and has started a website to sell the prints . 
 